{"questionId":"19462","questionHtml":"<p>State the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is decreasing.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)&nbsp; &nbsp;(C2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> seen as part of an inequality, <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for completely correct notation. Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for correct equivalent statement in words, for example “decreasing when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is greater than negative <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>”.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br></strong></em><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19462","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.T_11c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the values of x for which f(x) is decreasing.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}